<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-484-955  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 484 955.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Magazine  Oct 1990 v5 n10 p161(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Telecon Library Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AppleShare server. (ShirtPocket Software's EasyServer) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   ShirtPocket Software Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   EasyServer (Computer network software) (product introduction)Appleshare (Computer program) (equipment and supplies).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFile ServersThird-Party Vendors.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AppleShare ServerandM;While Apple Computer bows out of the AppleShare server market, ShirtPocketSoftware is stepping in with EasyServer.andP;  According to ShirtPocket Software,the high-performance, dedicated, standalone file server provides &quot;the speedof a Mac IIfx for the price of a Mac SE.&quot;andP;  EasyServer costs $1,995.andM;EasyServer comes configured for LocalTalk and equipped with a high-speed SCSIport.andP;  Ethernet and Token Ring options are also available.andM;The company claims EasyServer is the only third-party file server with theability to read and write Macintosh-formatted disks.andP;  AnyMacintosh-compatible storage device can be used as the server disk, includingCD-ROM, removable, and WORM drives The server disk can be connected to anyMacintosh computer if files need maintenance or repair, or if the server diskis replaced by a larger-capacity upgrade.andP;  If the file server crashes, userscan keep data online by employing EasyShare software or System 7.0's filesharing software.andM;For speed, EasyServer includes a coprocessor that handles network trafficwhile the main processor handles high-speed DMA SCSI data transfers.andP;  Becausenetwork operations and file accesses occur in parallel, EasyServerperformance does not deteriorate as the number of users increases.andM;ShirtPocket Software, P.O. Box 40666, Mesa, Ariz.andP;  85274, (602) 966-7667.andO;</TEXT></DOC>